  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nCurrently when running `forge test`, if your foundry.toml file includes invalid characters you get the following message:\r\n```\r\nError:\r\nunexpected character found: `;` at line 5 column 16\r\nunexpected character found: `;` at line 5 column 16\r\nunexpected character found: `;` at line 5 column 16\r\nunexpected character found: `;` at line 5 column 16\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt would be nice to give a clearer error message to direct the user to the file where the error originates from.\r\n\r\nSimilar errors occur if you don't include `solc=\"x.y.z\"` in the toml file but don't make it clear what the issue is or how to fix it.\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
